---
description: Apply when editing requirement specification files (`*.md` in `docs/specs`).
alwaysApply: true
globs:
  - "docs/specs/**/*.md"
---

When editing these files:
- In Russian prose, do not use the letter «ё»; use «е» instead (e.g. `все`, `еще`, `подъем`).
- Preserve document structure (table of contents, heading hierarchy).
- If a document has 3+ `##` sections, add a `## Table of Contents` section near the top with clickable links to each section (Markdown list format: `- [Text](#anchor)`).
- TOC anchors must follow GitHub style (as validated by `scripts/check-markdown-links.mjs`); update TOC when headings change.
- Do not delete existing requirements without explicit request; mark them as "deprecated" or "replaced" instead.
- When adding a new requirement, always include an identifier (for example `FR-001`, `NFR-010`) and short rationale.
- Add/maintain a `Related Documents` section when needed, with relative links to canonical artifacts (`docs/artifacts/*`, `docs/specs/*`, `docs/protocols/*`, `docs/architecture/*`).
